snippet.textDisplay:
It took 9 years for me to reach to this Song.!
And here am playing it in loop, sharing the mutual curiosities, imaginations and grief which i dont know why ...

might be i always water this thought. How beautiful it would've been if two was still one..
started thinking about it when i was a kid watching cricket, thinking about all the good players in team.

but slowly that changed to empathy towards the people who've suffered during partition, or still living with that memory, and people who just want to meet their dear ones again ...

snippet.textDisplay:
I am 30 years old Pakistani man. One of my dreams before I die is to visit India in my car. I want to cross the border with my national identity card & as the officer checks my documents, wave to the indians on the other side crossing into Pakistan. 

We share a common soil, common blood & language. What's keeping us apart?
